<head>



<title>CREATE-CHOOSER</title>

</head>



<body>



<div id="bodyContent">

	<h3><i>I create a chooser of values for a variable.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>CREATE-CHOOSER </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>substitute-text-area-for chooser-variable a-b-or-c         
substitute-text-area-for lower-left-corner-x 5    
substitute-text-area-for lower-left-corner-y 250 
substitute-text-area-for upper-right-corner-x 80   
substitute-text-area-for upper-right-corner-y 300
substitute-text-area-for chooser-default-selection 2 
substitute-text-area-for chooser-choices "2" "a" "c" "2.5" "5"
create-chooser 
  &quot;chooser-variable&quot;<i>&nbsp;; name of global variable</i>
  &quot;lower-left-corner-x&quot; &quot;lower-left-corner-y&quot;&nbsp;<i>; lower left corner </i>
  &quot;upper-right-corner-x&quot; &quot;upper-right-corner-y&quot;&nbsp;<i>; upper right corner</i>
  &quot;chooser-default-selection&quot;&nbsp;<i>; choice selected by default</i>
  chooser-choices<i>&nbsp;; choices quoted and separated by spaces</i>
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>All the parameters can be changed. It can also be edited within NetLogo 

	but those changes won't be saved. </p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>

	<a title="CREATE-PLOT" href="CREATE-PLOT.html">

	CREATE-PLOT</a>,

	<a title="CREATE-SLIDER" href="CREATE-SLIDER.html">

	CREATE-SLIDER</a>,

	<a title="CREATE-MONITOR" href="CREATE-MONITOR.html">

	CREATE-MONITOR</a> and

	<a title="CREATE-BUTTON" href="CREATE-LEFT-TURN-BUTTON.html">
	CREATE-LEFT-TURN-BUTTON</a> also create interface elements. </p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>This creates a NetLogo chooser for a global variable. In this example the 

	variable is named <i>a-b-or-c</i> and the choices are &quot;a&quot;, &quot;b&quot;, &quot;c&quot;, 
	&quot;2.5&quot;, and &quot;5&quot;. </p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </div>



